The exquisite design of the cars will not only immerse your child, but will also help them to develop a proper concept of firefighting vehicles. Salute to the firefighting heroes!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy and fun
reviews.reviewText: This toy and the tiny trucks have been through a lot. The struggle to not step on these is always intense but somehow they're still all intact. The small trucks are small so definitely not for kids that still put things in their mouths but a lot of fun. I like that you can turn the noise for the big truck on and off

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Awful. You get the tiny cars in the picture. Not the big car
reviews.reviewText: The picture is definitely not what it seems. I thought these never came. I took a picture of it with a soda next to it, so everyone has an idea of how big they actually are. If Christmas wasn't right around the corner, I'd send it back. These people are completely scamming people out of money, which is terrible especially around holiday season.Update : It's a lot smaller, so small that I just gave it to my child now. The little cars are wind up toys, so they'll drive for actually pretty good distances on their own after being wound up. The transporter car lights up and makes noise with batteries. So it did end up getting better. 1 star to 3 stars.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Very misleading photo.
reviews.reviewText: I was very excited to purchase this toy for my grandson who LOVES trucks. The photo shows a young child playing with the truck and it looks like a LARGE truck for an approximately 18 - 24 month old boy. When I received the package it was literally the size of a saltine cracker box. The truck was extremely smaller than the photo portrayed. I payed $30.00 for this toy which is way to much to pay for a small toy. If it was actually the size they make it seem it would be a good value but it is falsely advertised. I am very disappointed and am likely going to return it as it overpriced for the size. The actual size toy is worth about $15.00 in my opinion. You can see in MY photo that the toy is less then 14” long. And it is only 5-1/2” tall. It is about the size of a box of instant oatmeal. Sooo misleading of this company. Sooo disappointing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Kids loved it but picture deceiving
reviews.reviewText: My nephew loves it but marked down rating due to deceptive pictures. The truck is not as big as they are trying to show. All photos appear to be photo shopped. Pay attention to description measurements. Aside from that, sturdy construction and seems to be made well. He’s two and was able to open the back himself to drive the cars into the trailer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 14, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I bought this toy for my son who is super into cars and right now this happens to be his favorite toy, I am so happy he enjoys it! What I find appealing is that the smaller cars are easy for him to hold and play with. Definitely worth it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So Cute And The Perfect Size
reviews.reviewText: When I got my package, I was like... That is tiny. But when I opened it up, I was like: This Is The Perfect Size and Super Cute! It will fix in the toy box and won't take up a lot of space in it. Plus, if it was as big as everyone was hoping for, I would had, had no room for it. Again, Perfect if you don't have a lot of space in the toy box or on the floor. Plus my littles can hold the cars with easy, in their hands. An Even Bigger Perk.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Item is much smaller than ad portrays.
reviews.reviewText: The picture in the ad is very misleading. When it arrived I was very disappointed. It is drastically smaller than I expected. It is well made but nowhere near the size the picture portrays. The quality was good and very durable as advertised but the picture is way out of proportion. Not sure how they managed .to do that by using actual children in the picture, but it worked. I bought 2 of them ( yellow and red ones) based on the size represented. My grandkids still played with them and enjoyed them. Just beware. If you are impressed based on the picture, you will probably be disappointed too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Not near as large as they are represented in advertising photo. They look like what's in the photo but, much smaller than anticipated...

Very nice toy with bright colours. No assembly needed. Perfect size for my son to hold it and play. All smaller pieces can fit into the big one, super neat! The big truck has lights and sound. It keeps my son busy for a while
This quickly became my grandson’s favorite toy. So far very durable.
